# Common Rails 8 Mistakes to Avoid

- Do NOT use `render :json => ` (old syntax) — use `render json:`
- Do NOT use `attr_accessible` — removed in Rails 4+, use strong params
- Do NOT use `before_filter` — use `before_action`
- Do NOT use hash rockets in enum definitions for new code
- Do NOT skip `null: false` on required DB columns
- Do NOT use string column for enums — always integer
- Do NOT call `.all` without a scope in controllers — always scope to user
- Do NOT use `update_attributes` — use `update`
- Do NOT use `find_by_x` dynamic finders — use `find_by(x:)`
- Do NOT rescue Exception — rescue StandardError or specific subclasses
- Do NOT put logic in routes.rb
- Do NOT use `respond_to` blocks in API-only controllers
- Do NOT forget to add foreign_key constraints in migrations
- Do NOT use `validates_presence_of` — use `validates :field, presence: true`